Add the FreeBSD chflags option
	-f flags

and support flags in instck's last column
	/kernel	-rwxr--r--	root:*	schg,nostrip

Change the letter "n", "l", "s" to "nostrip", "ranlib", "strip" as
pseudo flags

see g05.sa:/usr/src/bin/ls/stat_flags.c for clues

Also make instck -G generate them.



Question: does install check the link count on the source file before it
unlinks it?  If the link count is >1 maybe we should NOT remove it?


